{"parse":{"title":"Republic of Tunisia International Prize for Islamic Studies","pageid":25282545,"revid":836509623,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Republic of Tunisia International Prize for Islamic Studies</b> or <b>World Award of the President of the Republic for Islamic Studies</b> is an award given by the President of Tunisia, <a href=\"/wiki/Zine_El_Abidine_Ben_Ali\" title=\"Zine El Abidine Ben Ali\">Zine El Abidine Ben Ali</a> since 2003 to reward those scholars and writers globally who have made significant contribution to Islamic studies annually. The prize is usually given at <a href=\"/wiki/Carthage_Palace\" title=\"Carthage Palace\">Carthage Palace</a> and the recipient is invited to meet with the president for the award ceremony.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recipients\">Recipients</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Republic_of_Tunisia_International_Prize_for_Islamic_Studies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Recipients\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><b>First World Award</b> -Awarded November 21, 2003 to <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mahmoud_Hamdi_Zaqzouq&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Mahmoud Hamdi Zaqzouq (page does not exist)\">Mahmoud Hamdi Zaqzouq</a>, Egyptian Minister of WAQF.</li>\n<li><b>Second World Award</b> -Awarded November 9, 2004, to Sheikh <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Habib_Belkhouja&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Habib Belkhouja (page does not exist)\">Habib Belkhouja</a>.</li>\n<li><b>Third World Award</b> -Awarded October 31, 2005, to <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sergio_Pallavicini&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Sergio Pallavicini (page does not exist)\">Sergio Pallavicini</a>,vice-president of the Italian Islamic Religious Community, and Imam of the Mosque of Milan.</li>\n<li><b>Fourth World Award</b>- Awarded October 19, 2006, to <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mohammed_H%27ssine_Fantar&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Mohammed H&#39;ssine Fantar (page does not exist)\">Mohammed H'ssine Fantar</a> .</li>\n<li><b>Fifth World Award</b>- Awarded October 8, 2007, to Dr. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rekaia_Taha_Jaber_Al_Alouani&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Rekaia Taha Jaber Al Alouani (page does not exist)\">Rekaia Taha Jaber Al Alouani</a>, professor at d\u00e9partement of Arab Language and Islamic Studies at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Bahrain\" title=\"University of Bahrain\">University of Bahrain</a>.</li>\n<li><b>Sixth World Award</b>, Awarded September 26, 2008 to Dr. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rawnak_Hassen_Hosni&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Rawnak Hassen Hosni (page does not exist)\">Rawnak Hassen Hosni</a>, professor at the University of Heriot and at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Durham\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University of Durham\">University of Durham</a>, Great Britain and to Professor <a href=\"/wiki/Daniel_Newman_(academic)\" title=\"Daniel Newman (academic)\">Daniel Newman</a>, professor at the Modern Languages and Cultures school at the University of Durham.</li>\n<li><b>Seventh World Award</b>, Awarded on September 16, 2009 to Spanish theologian Dr. <a href=\"/wiki/Juan_Jos%C3%A9_Tamayo\" title=\"Juan Jos\u00e9 Tamayo\">Juan Jos\u00e9 Tamayo</a> for his book entitled \"Islam: Culture, religion and politics\".</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Republic_of_Tunisia_International_Prize_for_Islamic_Studies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:/